It would be nice if JIRA Plugins have the ability to check the run-time environment prior to installation.

An example scenario would be as such:

A user has JIRA version 6.2.6 with JAVA 1.6 however when updating the HipChat plugin to the latest version using UPM , the installation process didn't complete without any obvious errors on the UI. 

!Jira-HipChat-Update-Progress-11-JUN-2015-0107PM.png|thumbnail!


From the logs the user could see this stack trace error :
{code}
Caused by: java.lang.UnsupportedClassVersionError: com/atlassian/plugins/hipchat/api/link/HipChatLinkProvider : Unsupported major.minor version 51.0
{code}

Which concludes that an upgrade of JAVA from 1.6 to 1.7 is needed to successfully complete the update.

