It is a common case for one issue's symptoms to be resolved by another fix. Currently, the only recourse is to connect the related issues using the "link" menu and resolve the supplemental issue as either NAI or Duplicate. When assessing risk in code changes scheduled for release, we need to review only those tickets that have code changes associated with them and which code changes resolved what. Historically, we would like to look up the tickets that were resolved by a given code change and, often times, the links are not made at the time of code submission (we find out after the fact that one change resolved others as well).
Please create a means to link stash or other repository code changes to various issues.

